    "created_at": "2012-09-24T18:00:24Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-09-24T18:00:24Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "My apologies - there is something IPython related going on here, I didn't notice the print statement.  The issue is that zmq sockets cannot be passed across a fork, and sys.stdout is linked to a zmq socket.  IPython is going to need to detect forks and discard (and possibly recreate) sockets when a fork happens.\n\nI don't know how the crash occurs in the parent process in master, that's super weird.  I would expect the child to crash, though.\n"
  },
